DStv is facing stiff competition from streaming services like Netflix as well as piracy, but it is fighting back by offering its subscribers an enhanced online experience through its DStv Now service. Through DStv Now subscribers can watch their favourite movies, TV programmes, and live sports on a wide range of devices. The service comes free with a DStv and PVR subscription and is available through a web app or iOS and Android mobile apps. MultiChoice continues to invest in the platform, and recent changes to the DStv Now web app include: MultiChoice Connected Video head of communications Richard Boorman told MyBroadband that there are many more new features to come. These enhancements include more personalisation features, improved recommendations, reduced data usage, and new usability features. The company has also made improvements to its DStv Now Android and iOS mobile apps, which include: “As with the web app, we’re also working on more personalisation features, improved recommendations, reduced data usage, and new usability features,” Boorman said. The screenshots below show the enhancements to the DStv Now web app. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-305584 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DStv-Now-Home-Page-640x373.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="373" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DStv-Now-Home-Page-640x373.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DStv-Now-Home-Page-600x350.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DStv-Now-Home-Page-768x448.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DStv-Now-Home-Page.jpg 1082w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-305586 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Revised-Promo-Rows-640x385.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="385" s